estellt. Das Buch ergänzt die Präsentation der Entwürfe um fünf Essays namhafter Autor*innen und einen Comic, der einen Tag in den Salons der Republik lebendig werden lässt.  aThe political climate of our time is being shaped by a dwindling ability to engage in public dialogue, putting democratic practices under increasing pressure. In order to counter the trend towards retreating into the realm of self-affirmation, we need new spaces in which public debate is not only tolerated but stimulated. With this in mind, students at RheinMain University of Applied Sciences designed centrally located salons in Berlin and Frankfurt/Main that could inspire interest in democratic engagement. In summer 2021, the German Architecture Museum will exhibit these designs. This book complements the exhibit with five essays by well-known authors, as well as a comic strip depicting a day in the life of the Salons of the Republic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aArchitektur. 4aDemokratie. 4aStadtentwicklung. 4aÖffentlichkeit. 7aARCHITECTURE / Individual Architects & Firms / General.2bisacsh  aArchitecture.  aDemocracy.  aPublic Sphere.  aUrban Studies.1 aCachola Schmal, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamphans, Marion, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKleine, Holger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKleine, Holger, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKunze, Ralf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLecointe, Jonas Aaron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMay, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRech, Johanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpee